hnology, innovation and policy.\", \"from\": 598, \"to\": 922, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 677, \"end\": 686, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Microsoft\", \"score\": 0.9999999982924237, \"rank\": 1.7074304603893843e-09, \"text\": \"Microsoft\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Microsoft\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Microsoft\"}, {\"begin\": 823, \"end\": 832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Hindu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4456619799273773e-24, \"text\": \"The Hindu\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Hindu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Hindu\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To get it in your inbox, subscribehere.)\", \"from\": 923, \"to\": 963, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even as CrowdStrike shared a fix to solve the Microsoft IT outage that brought down industries world over, people continued to face flight delays or cancellations in major airline hubs such as the U.S. and India over the weekend.\", \"from\": 965, \"to\": 1194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 973, \"end\": 984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CrowdStrike\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"CrowdStrike\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CrowdStrike\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CrowdStrike\"}, {\"begin\": 1011, \"end\": 1020, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Microsoft\", \"score\": 0.9999999982924237, \"rank\": 1.7074304603893843e-09, \"text\": \"Microsoft\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Microsoft\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Microsoft\"}, {\"begin\": 1171, \"end\": 1176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9999987890990325, \"rank\": 8.996046051767203e-07, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition to this,cyber security experts warned that phishing attempts might be on the rise, as malicious actors try to exploit the outage by pretending to be technical experts and offering to bring affected systems back to order.\", \"from\": 1195, \"to\": 1427, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Microsoft said 8.5 million devices with the Windows OS were impacted by the incident, stressing this made up less than 1% of all Windows-based machines.\", \"from\": 1428, \"to\": 1580, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1428, \"end\": 1437, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Microsoft\", \"score\": 0.9999999982924237, \"rank\": 1.7074304603893843e-09, \"text\": \"Microsoft\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Microsoft\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Microsoft\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The cause of theglobal IT outage on July 19 was a CrowdStrike software update that went wrong, shared the cybersecurity company that is based in Austin, Texas.\", \"from\": 1582, \"to\": 1741, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1632, \"end\": 1643, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CrowdStrike\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"CrowdStrike\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CrowdStrike\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CrowdStrike\"}, {\"begin\": 1727, \"end\": 1740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Circuit_of_the_Americas\", \"score\": 0.9999999999286047, \"rank\": 5.523697346638928e-11, \"text\": \"Austin, Texas\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Circuit_of_the_Americas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Circuit_of_the_Americas\"}, {\"begin\": 1727, \"end\": 1740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Circuit_of_the_Americas\", \"score\": 0.9999999999286047, \"rank\": 5.523697346638928e-11, \"text\": \"Austin, Texas\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Circuit_of_the_Americas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Circuit_of_the_Americas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Over the weekend, IT experts and engineers were working with companies across the world to recover the impacted systems and bring them back to normal, raising questions about anti-competitive controls and quality assurance standards in the cybersecurity market.\", \"from\": 1742, \"to\": 2003, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Russia tries to source advanced computer chips and other products in order to support its war against Ukraine, which it attacked in early 2022, but data from the U.S. Commerce Department shows thatsemiconductors and other clandestine goods shipped to the country via China and Hong Kong fell this year.\", \"from\": 2005, \"to\": 2307, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2005, \"end\": 2011, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999999996416591, \"rank\": 2.3616235813402675e-10, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 2107, \"end\": 2114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999999452088575, \"rank\": 5.4737928119517726e-08, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 2172, \"end\": 2191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Department_of_Commerce\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Commerce Department\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Department_of_Commerce\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Department_of_Commerce\"}, {\"begin\": 2272, \"end\": 2277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"