.S. laws.\", \"from\": 2575, \"to\": 2740, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2585, \"end\": 2591, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nvidia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nvidia\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nvidia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nvidia\"}, {\"begin\": 2642, \"end\": 2644, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6419148308299562e-17, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 2681, \"end\": 2687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999999996416591, \"rank\": 2.3616235813402675e-10, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 2730, \"end\": 2734, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.8437561007657602, \"rank\": 0.18515463740521296, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Intel also said it operates in strict accordance with U.S. export regulations and sanctions.\", \"from\": 2741, \"to\": 2833, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2741, \"end\": 2746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Intel\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.5835774264703494e-12, \"text\": \"Intel\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Intel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Intel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Generative AI will be playing a major role in the 2024 Paris Olympics, as a chatbot developed by Intel in collaboration with the International Olympic Committee (IOC) is set to make its debut during the historic games.Titled AthleteGPT, the chatbot is meant to help Olympic athletesby answering their questions, guiding them through the large venue, and assisting them when it comes to following local rules and regulations.\", \"from\": 2835, \"to\": 3259, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2846, \"end\": 2848, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6419148308299562e-17, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 2932, \"end\": 2937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Intel\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.5835774264703494e-12, \"text\": \"Intel\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Intel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Intel\"}, {\"begin\": 2964, \"end\": 3001, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Intel, a worldwide Olympic Partner since 2017, is also set to support 8K resolution live streaming experiences, so that fans can enjoy low-latency, high-definition streaming for 32 sporting events.\", \"from\": 3261, \"to\": 3458, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3261, \"end\": 3266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Intel\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.5835774264703494e-12, \"text\": \"Intel\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Intel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Intel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Published- July 22, 2024 11:55 am IST  technology (general)  Copyright\\u00a9 2025